peachment of President Donald J. Trump.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aConstitutional lawzUnited States. 0aImpeachmentszUnited States. 0aPresidentsxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 4aHistory : American History. 4aPolitics and Law : Congressional Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Constitutional Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / Executive Branch.2bisacsh1 aCaress, Stanley M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSanders, Robert M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848005340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438480053423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438480053/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles